Dear reader,

=C2=A0

Earlier this year, we launched the first quarterly installment of The Puck =
Private Conversation, powered by Orchestra, the strategy and communications=
 mega-agency, as yet=C2=A0another=C2=A0way to deliver on one of the foundin=
g principles at Puck: to reveal what executives, decision-makers, and our e=
lite readership=C2=A0really=C2=A0think about the high-level questions and p=
roblems affecting the industries we cover so closely.

=C2=A0

Today, I=E2=80=99m thrilled to announce the second installment of this grou=
ndbreaking series. This time, we=E2=80=99re focusing on how executives and =
industry insiders are navigating the post-election economic landscape: the =
potential impact of tariffs, trade wars, deregulation, changing tax regimes=
, and a hyper-charged political climate. We=E2=80=99re also diving more dee=
ply into how our audience of media consumers and producers, alike, are enga=
ging with an entertainment industry and information space that is more frac=
tured than ever.

=C2=A0

But remember, this is meant to be=C2=A0fun. The anonymous survey only takes=
 a few minutes to complete, and just like the first time, your responses wi=
ll be synthesized by my partner=C2=A0Baratunde Thurston, who will sift thro=
ugh the data and surface the most relevant and surprising insights. This da=
ta provides the sort of landscape analysis that other companies outsource t=
o consulting firms. Here at Puck, it=E2=80=99s just another benefit of memb=
ership. Thanks for your time, and I hope you=E2=80=99re as excited as I am =
to dig into the resultss.

